g powers and entitled to receive the benefit from operations of these entities hence these companies are identified as vies and are consolidated as if subsidiaries of the company we did not identify any additional vies in which we hold a significant interest the total consolidated vie assets and liabilities reflected on the companys balance sheet are as follows             assets             cash and cash equivalents             inventories               accounts receivable               tax recoverable               other receivables and deposits               goodwill               property plant and equipment net               intangible assets net                                 total assets not include amount due from intragroup companies                                 liabilities                 deferred income               accounts payable               accrued expenses and other payables               taxes payable               total current liabilities                                   f   the results of vies are as follows and are included in the consolidated statements of income of the company                           revenue             other income and gains               service costs not including service costs payable to intragroup companies             personnel cost             depreciation expense             amortization expense             administrative and other expenses                               income before provision for income taxes not including service costs payable to intragroup companies             income tax incomeprovision for income taxes                                net income             under the contractual arrangements with the vies the company has the power to direct activities of the vies and can have assets transferred freely out of the vies without restrictions therefore the company considers that there is no asset of vies that can only be used to settle obligations of the respective vies except for registered capital and prc statutory reserves of vies as of april   and may   since the vies are incorporated as limited liability companies under the prc company law creditors of the vies do not have recourse to the general credit of the company there is currently no contractual arrangement that would require the company to provide additional financial support to the vies as the company is conducting certain businesses mainly through its vies the company may provide such support on a discretionary basis in the future which could expose the company to a loss note  – segmental analysis information of the companys business segment is as follows                            revenue from              telecommunications                                segment loss from                  telecommunications            motor vehicle technical  emission inspection                                              depreciation  amortization expenses                  telecommunications              motor vehicle technical  emission inspection                                                  segment assets                  telecommunications              motor vehicle technical  emission inspection                                                  capital expenditure                  telecommunications              motor vehicle technical  emission inspection                              f note  – capital commitments capital commitment that related to the companys car inspection business is as follows                           contracted but not provided for property plant and equipment   within  year             note  – related party transaction                             revenue              redtone mex sdn bhd              shanghai huili telecommunications co ltd               cost of sales                  shanghai huili telecommunications co ltd                                  total              f   note   restatements   during the course of internal evaluation our accounting staff found class